  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Social Model, an alternative for educational transformation</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UNESCO Office in Mexico will collaborate with and NGO Fundaci&#xF3;n Bailleres in a project of social transformation of two school communities in Mexico City. After the 2017 earthquakes, the NGO decided to finance school reconstruction since more than 5000 schools were damaged. Their involvement with the communities has transformed into building new schools and involving the entire community in the design project. They have built capacity with school leadership, parents and education authorities to enable a participatory school model that will promote social cohesion in those communities. UNESCO Mexico will provide technical assistance to systematize the experience and will monitor the school communities for two years to identify the impact of this project and its sustainability capacity.</narrative>
  </description>
